definitions.definition: Any of several small turtles of the families Emydidae and Geoemydidae found throughout the world .
Any of several small turtles native to North America that live in brackish or fresh water , especially the diamondback terrapin ( Malaclemys terrapin ).
The flesh of such a turtle used as food .

main_definition: ( countable ) Any of several small turtles of the families Emydidae and Geoemydidae found throughout the world .
secondary_definitions: ( countable , obsolete ) Any of several small turtles native to North America that live in brackish or fresh water , especially the diamondback terrapin ( Malaclemys terrapin ).
( uncountable , obsolete ) The flesh of such a turtle used as food .
